<% content_for :title, "Frequently Asked Questions" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "Common questions about Prowl — product page monitoring, scans, alerts, billing, and troubleshooting for Shopify merchants." %>

<div class="support-hero">
  <h1>Frequently asked questions</h1>
  <p>Quick answers to common questions about Prowl.</p>
</div>

<div class="support-content">
  <div class="support-section">
    <h2>General</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">
        What does Prowl do?
        <span class="faq-arrow">&#9660;</span>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Prowl monitors your Shopify product pages every day for broken functionality — things like missing Add to Cart buttons, broken variant selectors, images that won't load, and missing prices. When something breaks, you get an alert with a screenshot, a description of the issue, and a suggested fix.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">
        How is Prowl different from uptime monitoring?
        <span class="faq-arrow">&#9660;</span>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Uptime monitors only check if your site is up or down. Prowl goes deeper — it loads your product pages in a real browser, checks that every element works correctly, and tests the actual purchase flow by clicking Add to Cart and verifying the item reaches the cart. Your site can be "up" while your Add to Cart button is completely broken. Prowl catches that.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">
        Does Prowl work with my theme?
        <span class="faq-arrow">&#9660;</span>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Yes. Prowl works with every Shopify theme — free themes, paid themes, and custom themes. No code changes or configuration are required. Prowl visits your pages the same way a customer would and checks for issues regardless of your theme.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">
        Does Prowl affect my store's performance or speed?
        <span class="faq-arrow">&#9660;</span>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        No. Prowl scans your pages from our servers — it doesn't install any scripts, snippets, or code on your storefront. It visits your product pages like a regular customer would. Your store's speed and customer experience are not affected.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="support-section">
    <h2>Scanning</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">
        How often does Prowl scan my product pages?
        <span class="faq-arrow">&#9660;</span>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Prowl runs automated scans once per day at 6:00 AM UTC. You can also trigger a scan manually at any time by clicking "Scan now" on any product page inside the app. Deep scans (which include full purchase flow testing) run on the first scan, when critical issues are open, and weekly on Mondays.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">
        How many product pages can I monitor?
        <span class="faq-arrow">&#9660;</span>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        You can monitor up to 3 product pages. We recommend selecting your highest-traffic or highest-revenue products. We're planning to increase this limit in a future update.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">
        What does Prowl check during a scan?
        <span class="faq-arrow">&#9660;</span>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        During each scan, Prowl checks: Add to Cart button presence and functionality, variant selector behavior, product image loading, price visibility, JavaScript errors, theme rendering issues, and page load speed. During deep scans, Prowl also tests the full purchase flow — selecting a variant, clicking Add to Cart, and verifying the item reaches the cart.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">
        Does the purchase flow test create real orders?
        <span class="faq-arrow">&#9660;</span>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        No. Prowl only tests up to the cart stage — it adds an item to the cart, verifies it was added successfully, and then removes it. It never proceeds to checkout, enters payment information, or creates orders.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="support-section">
    <h2>Alerts</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">
        When will I get an alert?
        <span class="faq-arrow">&#9660;</span>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Prowl sends alerts for high-severity issues only — problems that directly prevent customers from purchasing. High-confidence issues (confirmed by AI visual analysis) trigger an alert immediately on first detection. Lower-confidence issues are re-checked on the next scan before alerting, to avoid false alarms.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">
        How do I stop getting alerts for an issue I'm aware of?
        <span class="faq-arrow">&#9660;</span>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Click "Acknowledge" on the issue detail page inside the app, or click the acknowledge link in the alert email. Once acknowledged, Prowl stops sending emails about that specific issue. The issue will still appear in your dashboard so you can track it.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">
        Can I change where alert emails are sent?
        <span class="faq-arrow">&#9660;</span>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Yes. Go to Settings inside the Prowl app and enter a custom alert email address. By default, alerts go to your Shopify store owner email.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="support-section">
    <h2>Billing</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">
        How much does Prowl cost?
        <span class="faq-arrow">&#9660;</span>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Prowl costs $10/month, billed through Shopify. There's a 14-day free trial with full access to all features — no limitations during the trial period.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">
        How do I cancel my subscription?
        <span class="faq-arrow">&#9660;</span>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        You can cancel at any time by uninstalling the Prowl app from your Shopify admin. Your subscription is managed through Shopify's billing system, so there are no separate cancellation steps. You won't be charged after uninstalling.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">
        Do I get charged during the free trial?
        <span class="faq-arrow">&#9660;</span>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        No. Your 14-day free trial includes full access to every feature. You'll only be charged after the trial ends. If you uninstall before the trial expires, you won't be charged at all.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="support-section" style="text-align: center;">
    <h2>Still have questions?</h2>
    <p>We're here to help. Send us a message and we'll get back to you within 24 hours.</p>
    <a href="/support/contact" class="btn-submit" style="display: inline-block; text-decoration: none; margin-top: 8px;">Contact support</a>
  </div>
</div>
